title: Grateful Dead Live at Springer's Inn Portland on 1970-01-16
description:
Set 1

Casey Jones, Mama Tried, Black Peter, Hard To Handle, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, High Time, Good Lovin'-> Drums-> Good Lovin', Dancin' In The Streets, Alligator-> Drums-> The Eleven Jam-> Death Don't Have No Mercy

Set 2

Cumberland Blues, Me & My Uncle-> Dire Wolf, Uncle John's Band, Easy Wind, Cryptical Envelopement-> Drums-> The Other One-> Cryptical Envelopement-> Cosmic Charlie

Other artist(s): River

reviews.review_text: - Good, all-in-all. Especially good towards the end, with hot renditions of Easy Wind, Dire Wolf, etc.

Live Dead announcer says the band has a new album out called 'LIVE DEAD'
Yes, the time machine was properly calibrated?
However this is crack of dawn 1970 and LIVE DEAD is already way in the rear view mirror.
There is an ELEVEN jam > Death Don't

Any problems with this show are related to cuts 
but not to effort in performance.
Thanks for Sound Improvements.
This show is over the top!
Good Ol' Grateful Dead.

Dire Wolf in 1970 now that is sweetness...

Check out the guitar intro for Uncle John's Band
"This song is related to Morning Dew" -Jerry

Easy Wind- They didn't play this often but it sure rocked!

And some Anthem of the Sun.
Crypitcal>Drums>Other1>Cryptical

"Sliding on ice"
Remaster is on point Thanks for your efforts.  I am really digging it.
